  "body": "- [ X ] I've [opened a support ticket](https://trufflesuite.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/requests/new) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nAs a developer on new blockchain stacks I want to develop the ability to compile solidity for Solana and Substrate (Polkadot, Astar network, and many more). This will help developers like myself reach a much bigger market for my solidity smart contract deployment.\r\n\r\nAs a result I have to used the [Solang](https://github.com/hyperledger/solang) compiler.\r\n\r\nTruffle has made majority of the deployment work across multiple files extremely easy, especially when these files have address inputs that are dependencies upon other files being deployed upon creation.\r\n\r\n- Would there be any interest to include Solang compiler instead of Solc for deployment?\r\n- What would be the best way to include Solang?\r\n",
